  lines:
  - positionIndex: 1
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: "Sir Mendel\u2026 is this really the famous karenderya you were talking
      about? It looks\u2026 uh, a little quiet.\r\n"
  - positionIndex: 0
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: "Don\u2019t be fooled by appearances, [playerName]! Aleng Merly is an incredible
      cook. Her dishes are well loved in all of MendVille. Especially my favorite\u2014Laing\u2026
      or as we Bicolanos call it, Natong.\r"
  - positionIndex: 3
    spriteIndex: -1
    text: '[They look around. Mendel calls out.]'
  - positionIndex: 0
    spriteIndex: 0
    text: Aleng Merly? Are you here?
  - positionIndex: 1
    spriteIndex: 2
    text: "Hello? We\u2019d like to order something to eat!\n"
  - positionIndex: 3
    spriteIndex: -1
    text: "[After a few calls, a woman slowly appears from the kitchen\u2014Aleng
      Merly. She looks surprised to see customers.]"
  - positionIndex: 2
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: "Ay! Customers? Oh no\u2026 I wasn\u2019t expecting anyone today!\r\n"
  - positionIndex: 0
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: "Why so surprised, Aleng Merly? This is the most famous karenderya in town!\r"
  - positionIndex: 2
    spriteIndex: 2
    text: "Not anymore, Sir Mendel. I can\u2019t cook my best dishes these days.
      My garden doesn\u2019t grow the right ingredients anymore\u2026 and without
      them, I can only serve what\u2019s easy to buy in the market\u2014hotdogs,
      longganisa, and canned food.\r"
  - positionIndex: 1
    spriteIndex: 2
    text: "So\u2026 you mean your special dishes are impossible to cook now?\r"
  - positionIndex: 2
    spriteIndex: 3
    text: "Yes\u2026 especially Natong. The taro leaves in my garden are all the
      dark green ones\u2014the itchy kind. The good ones, the light green taro leaves,
      don\u2019t grow here anymore. Without them, I can\u2019t serve my signature
      Laing."
  - positionIndex: 0
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: 'Ah, [playerName]! This is the perfect challenge for you. Just like with
      pea pods, this problem can be solved through crossbreeding traits.

'
  - positionIndex: 1
    spriteIndex: 2
    text: "You mean\u2026 we can cross the taro plants to produce the non-itchy light
      green leaves?\r"
  - positionIndex: 0
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: "Exactly! If we can produce the right kind of taro, Aleng Merly can cook
      her Laing again.\r\r"
  - positionIndex: 2
    spriteIndex: 1
    text: "But for now\u2026 I can only serve you hotdogs. I hope you don\u2019t
      mind.\r"
  - positionIndex: 1
    spriteIndex: 0
    text: "Hotdogs are fine, Aleng Merly\u2026 but let\u2019s work on bringing your
      famous dishes back!\r"
  - positionIndex: 0
    spriteIndex: 0
    text: "Task 2 begins now, [playerName] Your goal is to cross the taro leaves
      and produce the light green, non-itchy variety.\r\r"
